The onset of cooler weather in Brazilduring the southern hemisphere winter is expected to have astabilising effect on a weak coffee market, West German tradesources said.    "The annual fear of frost in Brazil will probably grip themarket sometime this month until June or early July," one tradersaid.    The trade believes the International Coffee Organization(ICO) is unlikely to tackle the re-introduction of quotasbefore its September meeting and until then the market will notsee any unexpected sharp moves in either direction. REUTER&#3;